Milestone 0: Gym Members Data Analysis and Performance Improvement Prediction
​Project Overview - Group 6
This project develops advanced predictive models to forecast muscle mass improvement in gym members by leveraging comprehensive fitness tracking data and cutting-edge machine learning analytics to enable personalized training optimization and enhanced member outcomes.
​Problem & Research Questions
​RQ1: What factors most significantly influence muscle mass improvement outcomes?
​RQ2: Can we accurately predict muscle gain using member activity patterns?
​Hypothesis: Training consistency and balanced exercise intensity drive optimal performance gains.
​Datasets & Methods
​Program summary dataset containing comprehensive gym program analytics and metrics
​Member exercise tracking data with demographics, sessions, and performance indicators
​Advanced ML techniques: Random Forest and Linear Regression modeling
​Expected Outcomes
​Robust predictive model with interactive analytical dashboard for muscle improvement forecasting
​Impact & Significance
​Revolutionized gym management decisions and data-driven personalized fitness interventions
​Tools & Technologies
​Python ecosystem: Pandas, Scikit-learn, PyTorch for comprehensive data science analysis
